6 References



History[edit]
Coravin, Inc. was founded in 2011 by Greg Lambrecht, a Massachusetts Institute of Technology graduate and medical device inventor. Nick Lazaris, the former CEO of Keurig, joined as CEO.[2]
On July 29, 2013, Coravin launched its first product, the Coravin 1000 System. In September 2014, Coravin announced the opening of their European Headquarters, Coravin B.V., located in Amsterdam.[3] Frederic Levy, former Nespresso executive was appointed CEO in February, 2015.[4] By June 2015, Coravin, Inc. announced that it had secured $13.6 million in Series C-1 financing.[5]
